<br>
Well the young boy is just learning his craft but hopes to provide joy to the travelers and hopes one day to meet friends for adventure.  He walks over to a table by the chimney and lets the heat from the fire soak into his hands.  Bammar pulls out his new mandolin and starts to strum it hoping to finger a new tune.  The young boy always seems nervous and twitches as he cannot seem to stay still too long.  After a few seconds pause he starts strumming through a melodic tune.  His voice hits the air as he sings of a warrior that has found a red gem in his travels hoping to return it to a young princess. This song gives a tale of the fighter hoping to win her heart with this gem.  It took a valiant triumph over a vampire and his skeletal horde. The tune is rather loud but seems to bring emotion from the young boys heart.  <br>
<br>
The other patrons look up.  The young bard does not look over just yet to see the reaction from the song is taken by the others.  Soon he may find out but he just keeps strumming his mandolin a while further and signals for the barmaid.  He thinks a small glass of brandy might bring fire into his hands and throat for further songs this night.<br>
<br>
He says to the barmaid, &quot;Young lady can I get a drink, Yes can I get a drink? Yes, Yes, That would be good, Yes that would be good.&quot;  He talks fast and often repeats himself.  This is a trait from birth and seems to be due to stuttering.  Sometimes he feels this is a god forsaken evil birthright from Prexus, but when he sings it is nothing like this.  His words seem to come out smooth and wonderful.  Prexus did grant him this fine gift and hopefully he can make it help him in his quest for fun and adventure.  He hopes the patrons feel the same way but with drinking and carousing, one never knows.<br>
<br>
Bammar<br>
Young Bard of Prexus <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showPrevMessage?topicID=14.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showNextMessage?topicID=14.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.threadControl?topicID=14.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=14.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=14.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="firionaviefrm1">Firiona Vie General Chat<option value="firionaviefrm9">OT/OOC Forum<option value="firionaviefrm4">The Soapbox<option value="firionaviefrm62">In the Real Life News<option value="firionaviefrm58">Telegrams!<option value="firionaviefrm47">Guilds and Associations<option value="firionaviefrm10">A Bard for a Day<option value="firionaviefrm23">Hero Heart Tavern<option value="firionaviefrm15">The Polling Booth<option value="firionaviefrm40">Kudos!<option value="firionaviefrm